1
00:00:00,967 --> 00:00:03,267
<i>That man's death has
something to do</i>

2
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:06,933
<i>with the hidden secret
of Hotel 88.</i>

3
00:00:07,067 --> 00:00:08,933
<i> I love you, Luna.</i>

4
00:00:09,067 --> 00:00:11,067
<i> I love you, Gio.</i>

5
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,467
<i>And I will never leave
your side again.</i>

6
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:14,733
<i> Aah!</i>

7
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:18,500
<i>- Aah!
- Aah!</i>

8
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> "Sir Andy."</i>

9
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,867
<i> That's what they called him.</i>

10
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,533
<i>He was the one who
had you abducted?</i>

11
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:25,600
<i>They're also looking
for the treasure.</i>

12
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:26,600
<i> What treasure?</i>

13
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:29,633
<i>There's a buried treasure
in Hotel 88.</i>

14
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:36,133
If that's true, why are you
only telling me this now?

15
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,367
Because I'm running
out of time.

16
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:41,300
A lot of people already know
the secret.

17
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:45,300
I'm also looking for my father
because of that treasure.

18
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:51,533
I've known about the arson
incident even before.

19
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:54,733
My father told me it was to
pressure Michael Fernandez

20
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:57,933
into selling them
the hotel.

21
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,000
That way, they can get
the buried treasure.

22
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:05,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:01:05,433 --> 00:01:06,600
"They?"

24
00:01:08,133 --> 00:01:10,000
Who exactly are they?

25
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:11,767
Who were those people
with your father?

26
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,900
He didn't tell me,

27
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,700
but he didn't
do it alone.

28
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:20,667
Now, if this Sir Andy
I heard

29
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,633
is the same
as Andy Arellano,

30
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:24,933
it's possible that he was
the one with Papa.

31
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:32,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:47,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:43,000
It's all messed up, Edward.

34
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:44,567
First, the death
of Peter, Luna's ex,

35
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,367
then the hotel having
fewer guests

36
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,867
because of what happened.

37
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:50,167
Luna suddenly ran away
earlier

38
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:52,167
and now, this issue
with investors.

39
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:54,367
Problems keep piling up!
It's exhausting!

40
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:57,600
I feel like my mind
is going to explode!

41
00:02:57,733 --> 00:02:59,100
Jade, Jade, Jade.

42
00:02:59,233 --> 00:03:00,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:01,300
Jade.

44
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:04,233
Jade, calm down.

45
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:08,233
Inhale. Exhale.

46
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:12,300
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [JADE BREATHING HEAVILY]

47
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:14,700
Come on. Breathe with me.

48
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:15,800
Inhale.

49
00:03:18,967 --> 00:03:20,167
Exhale.

50
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:23,567
One more?

51
00:03:25,233 --> 00:03:26,467
I'm okay now.

52
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:28,633
Thank you.

53
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:33,300
Um...

54
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:38,833
Edward...

55
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:45,333
Maybe it'd be best
for you...

56
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:47,200
not to come here
for now.

57
00:03:49,067 --> 00:03:50,267
Why?

58
00:03:51,767 --> 00:03:53,767
Didn't you hear
what I said earlier?

59
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:58,333
Edward, our family is a mess,
and Uncle Andy--

60
00:03:58,467 --> 00:04:00,567
Jade, I talked to Dad.

61
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:02,367
His conscience is clear.

62
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,867
He didn't do
anything wrong.

63
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,233
But Leon...

64
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:07,800
Jade, whatever
Leon's issue is,

65
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:09,933
then that's his problem,
okay?

66
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:13,900
We shouldn't let it
affect us.

67
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:22,200
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

68
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:29,900
Well?

69
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:34,000
We are losing everything!

70
00:04:34,767 --> 00:04:36,200
The hotel...

71
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:38,300
Have you found Juan?

72
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:41,000
I had your men look for him,
but still nothing.

73
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:44,467
I even went as far as
searching the next town.

74
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,967
What if he tells on me?

75
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,233
Leon will get more
suspicious of me.

76
00:04:49,367 --> 00:04:51,200
As long as Juan
didn't see you,

77
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:52,967
you shouldn't worry.

78
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:55,000
He can't prove
it was you.

79
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:58,800
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:04:58,933 --> 00:05:00,367
What we should do...

81
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,833
is remove all of your
traces here.

82
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,900
We have to clean it up
and not leave anything behind.

83
00:05:13,667 --> 00:05:16,833
Okay, I'll tell my men.

84
00:05:18,467 --> 00:05:19,867
You have to hide.

85
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:22,600
Go somewhere far.

86
00:05:22,733 --> 00:05:24,433
You're not safe here
anymore.

87
00:05:24,567 --> 00:05:26,367
But Papa and I still
have a mission.

88
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,733
[SCOFFS] You'll put that first
over your life?

89
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:32,867
If we're right that it was Andy
Arellano who had you abducted...

90
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,667
he has strong connections
here in this island.

91
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,467
- I'm not afraid of him.
- Stop it, will you?

92
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,467
You're lucky you were
able to escape.

93
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:48,933
Trust me.
Get out of this island.

94
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:55,267
But before I leave, I'll report
that Andy to the cops.

95
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,433
No! Don't do that!

96
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:59,900
I saw one of your abductors
leave the station.

97
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,967
What if the cops
are involved in this?

98
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:06,067
- Even so!
- Are you insane?

99
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:08,667
My life is already
in danger,

100
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:12,400
so I'll take my chances
and report to the cops.

101
00:06:13,467 --> 00:06:16,000
Just make sure that you
make it out alive.

102
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:19,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

103
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:21,967
[CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

104
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:28,900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,733
[CARLOS] How low can you get,
Martin?!

106
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:36,067
You know Uncle Ronald,
and how conservative he is.

107
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,267
I had to--

108
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,367
<i> What?!</i>

109
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,100
<i> Come on, say it!</i>

110
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,733
That you had to lie?

111
00:06:43,367 --> 00:06:45,567
I'm going to tell him
the truth.

112
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,400
I just need him
to sign first.

113
00:06:47,533 --> 00:06:50,500
<i>Are you really
that desperate?</i>

114
00:06:50,633 --> 00:06:52,467
Martin, you should be ashamed!

115
00:06:53,233 --> 00:06:55,000
<i> Our industry is small.</i>

116
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:59,267
<i>Reputation travels faster
than any other contracts.</i>

117
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:02,767
What will my business
partners say?

118
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,033
I'm sorry, Dad.

119
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,600
You know what?
Just come back here.

120
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:13,400
What? No!

121
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,467
<i> You know, Martin,</i>

122
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,733
there's nothing else you can do
for that hotel.

123
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:21,633
<i>Have you forgotten
what I taught you?</i>

124
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:24,767
<i>We cut on losses,
and then we walk away.</i>

125
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,700
And that's what
you're going to do.

126
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:31,267
I can't just leave
the hotel like this.

127
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,900
<i> Do you know what I see?</i>

128
00:07:35,467 --> 00:07:39,433
You are no longer
an asset, Martin.

129
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:41,700
<i> You are a liability.</i>

130
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:53,500
Sir, let's call it
a night.

131
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:55,033
You've had too much
to drink.

132
00:07:57,233 --> 00:07:58,800
Why do you care?

133
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:04,200
- I'll take you to your room.
- I said no!

134
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,500
Just go away.

135
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:10,633
You might log this
as overtime

136
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:12,900
even though I didn't
ask you to stay.

137
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:17,067
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

138
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,700
It's my choice to stay.

139
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:20,633
And I don't want you to stay!

140
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:22,967
Leave.

141
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:25,467
Leave!

142
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:32,633
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:40,867
[EXHALES SHARPLY, BURPS]

144
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:48,700
He made Sari leave
while getting himself drunk.

145
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,533
You mean Martin
is alone there?

146
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:55,700
- I'll go check on him.
- Hey, no! No need.

147
00:08:55,867 --> 00:08:58,333
He told Sari to leave,
but she didn't.

148
00:08:58,467 --> 00:09:00,133
She's still keeping an eye
on him.

149
00:09:00,267 --> 00:09:03,100
Besides, Sari won't leave
your brother alone.

150
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:13,100
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,333
I'm worried about him.
I'll go there.

152
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:20,433
- No, don't!
- No!

153
00:09:20,567 --> 00:09:22,233
Sir Martin might just get
upset with you.

154
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:26,267
I think he needs
to be alone.

155
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,700
- You know, space.
- I agree.

156
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,067
[KIKO] Oh.

157
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,767
You're home late.

158
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:36,300
Yeah, sorry I forgot
to message.

159
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:37,967
Where have you been?

160
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:41,000
- Huh?
- I said, "Where have you been?"

161
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,067
Just around the area.

162
00:09:44,733 --> 00:09:48,300
Wow! You seem in a good
mood.

163
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:51,033
You came from the
police station

164
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:53,933
because you're being pinned
for Peter's death, right?

165
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:54,933
Huh?

166
00:09:56,867 --> 00:09:58,133
Oh. Yes.

167
00:09:58,267 --> 00:09:59,933
And you're even smiling?

168
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:02,600
- Why? Is that wrong?
- [KIKO] No.

169
00:10:02,767 --> 00:10:07,367
We just find it a bit...
strange. Right?

170
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:08,367
That's all.

171
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,067
Yeah, it's weird.

172
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:14,333
All I can say is that the bad
things that are happening

173
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:17,867
will turn into happy moments.

174
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,300
Okay?

175
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:21,067
So, just keep the faith.

176
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:25,667
So, Monette...

177
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,333
Raphie...

178
00:10:31,033 --> 00:10:32,000
Kiko...

179
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:33,867
Enjoy life.

180
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,767
What's with him?

181
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:41,367
Well, if he's high, I have
nothing to do with it.

182
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:44,033
- I swear.
- Silly!

183
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,167
So, Raphie...

184
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,900
Enjoy life. [CHUCKLES]

185
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:50,667
- Enjoy life, sis.
- Enjoy life.

186
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:52,833
Enjoy, sir.

187
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:01,367
[GRUNTS] Ow.

188
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:04,733
Sir.

189
00:11:06,167 --> 00:11:08,100
You never listen, do you?

190
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,200
You haven't left yet?

191
00:11:12,133 --> 00:11:14,133
Yes, I'm stubborn.

192
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:16,200
My grandfather
told me that, too.

193
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,200
[SNIFFS]

194
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:20,300
Just leave me alone.

195
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:26,233
It's fine since
my stepfather said...

196
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:31,233
"You are no longer an asset,
Martin.

197
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:34,200
You are a liability!"

198
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:35,900
[CHUCKLES]

199
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:41,133
[CHUCKLING]

200
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:45,400
Sir, I will take you
to your room.

201
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:46,333
Let's go.

202
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:49,800
It's the truth, though.

203
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:54,833
I am a liability.

204
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:02,767
Even Papa,
who was my own blood...

205
00:12:02,767 --> 00:12:06,233
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

206
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:08,833
He would always force me
to go back to Mama.

207
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,733
And it's all because...

208
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:17,800
I'm a burden.

209
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:20,333
[SCOFFS]

210
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:25,967
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:12:25,967 --> 00:12:27,067
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

212
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:35,433
But, fine...

213
00:12:38,767 --> 00:12:40,233
I'll forgive you.

214
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:44,400
You're already dead anyway.
[CHUCKLES]

215
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:53,100
I understand why he did that.

216
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:59,533
He said he was just thinking
about Mama's feelings back then.

217
00:13:02,533 --> 00:13:04,300
But what about me?

218
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:11,867
What about my feelings?

219
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:22,900
[SNIFFLES]

220
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:29,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

221
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,200
I don't want to go back there.

222
00:13:32,367 --> 00:13:34,433
I don't want to live under
the same roof as them!

223
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:35,967
It's suffocating me!

224
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:39,467
It's so toxic.

225
00:13:39,467 --> 00:13:45,200
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

226
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,433
[EXHALES DEEPLY] Yes.

227
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:53,967
He let me use his surname.

228
00:13:57,100 --> 00:14:00,167
But I have to pay for it
for the rest of my life.

229
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,433
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

230
00:14:04,433 --> 00:14:06,367
Dad even told me...

231
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:10,100
"I accept you."

232
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:13,167
"I accept you, son."

233
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,267
[SOBS]
But do you know the truth?

234
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:23,567
He doesn't accept me.

235
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,400
[SNIFFLES] He doesn't.

236
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:36,100
I am not good enough.

237
00:14:45,067 --> 00:14:47,867
I will never be good enough.

238
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:51,400
Never.

239
00:14:53,567 --> 00:14:54,567
No.

240
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:59,300
In his eyes, I'm a bastard

241
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:01,133
born out of a mistake.

242
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,333
[SNIFFLES]

243
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:12,000
That's why I have
to be perfect, Sari.

244
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:15,467
[SNIFFLES]

245
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:22,367
That's why...

246
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:29,333
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:37,633
[SNIFFLES] I'm sick of it.

248
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:41,533
It's exhausting, Sari.

249
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,967
I'm so tired.

250
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:50,500
I'm so tired.

251
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:58,267
Leon, we need to talk.

252
00:16:00,967 --> 00:16:03,467
I know why you don't want Uncle
Andy to be our business partner.

253
00:16:04,467 --> 00:16:05,600
It's good that you
agree with me.

254
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,933
It has something to do
with Sandro Soliman, right?

255
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:15,100
I told you not to mention
that name again!

256
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,667
So, are we going
to talk

257
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:19,633
- or should I shout his name--
- Justin!

258
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:22,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:23,400
Let's go there.

260
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:30,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

261
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:37,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

262
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:44,200
[JUAN] Sir.

263
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,667
Juan?

264
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:50,300
- You're Juan Soliman, right?
- Yes.

265
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:52,233
What happened to you?

266
00:16:52,233 --> 00:16:54,033
That's why I came here.

267
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,767
I want to report what
happened to me.

268
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:00,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:04,200
[KEYPAD CLACKING]

270
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,500
Alright.

271
00:17:07,133 --> 00:17:09,533
Syvera, Chief was looking
for you earlier.

272
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:11,167
I think he needs something.

273
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:13,200
I'll take it from here.
You can go.

274
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:16,700
Okay. Go with Marina.

275
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,067
Let's go.

276
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:28,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

277
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:32,367
I don't know what part
of Isla Kaluguran it was.

278
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:34,500
But what I heard was clear.

279
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:36,433
Andy.

280
00:17:37,633 --> 00:17:40,333
And I believe
it was Andy Arellano.

281
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:47,267
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:50,533
Let me ask again.

283
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:52,800
Andy Arellano?

284
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,567
You're saying he was
the one who abducted you?

285
00:17:58,167 --> 00:18:00,467
With so many people named Andy
on the island,

286
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:03,300
how can you be sure
it was Andy Arellano?

287
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:07,467
Andy Arellano was the only one
my father mentioned back then.

288
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:11,900
And when he asked me questions
while he tortured me,

289
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,500
he knew too much
about my father.

290
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:20,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,533
Is there anyone else who knows

292
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,433
that Arellano was the one
who abducted you?

293
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:31,900
No.

294
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:38,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

295
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:40,633
Okay.

296
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:43,900
Please sign this.

297
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,933
This is your statement.

298
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:52,900
Juan.

299
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:54,933
I'm amazed at your courage.

300
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:57,433
You're going against
an Arellano,

301
00:18:57,433 --> 00:18:58,600
but you're not scared.

302
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,900
Because I'm sure of what I said.

303
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:06,000
Sign it. Please hurry up.

304
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:12,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

305
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:17,900
So, are you going
to arrest Arellano?

306
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:20,333
I'll go with you to
the medical examiner first.

307
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:23,333
We need to file it
for this report.

308
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:24,867
Wait here.

309
00:19:30,633 --> 00:19:33,333
I know Sandro was involved in
burning this hotel down before.

310
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:35,833
He must've been working
with Uncle Andy.

311
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:37,500
That's what you're
not telling us, right?

312
00:19:38,367 --> 00:19:39,433
Where'd you get
that information?

313
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:41,600
Juan stayed in this hotel.

314
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:43,633
He's Sandro's son.

315
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:45,833
How can you be sure--

316
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:48,000
[JUSTIN] I saw you go
inside Sandro's house.

317
00:19:49,667 --> 00:19:50,600
That's right.

318
00:19:51,467 --> 00:19:52,533
I followed you.

319
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:54,800
But I'm right, aren't I?

320
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:57,333
Around the same time
Juan arrived,

321
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:59,000
I stopped him from
targeting you because he knew

322
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,967
you were looking for
information about his father.

323
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,533
He's looking for Sandro?

324
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:07,367
[JUSTIN] Yes.

325
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:10,600
Since then, we've been working
together to find his father.

326
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,600
You're helping him?

327
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,900
Had you told me why you
were looking for that person,

328
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:16,667
I wouldn't have asked
anyone else for an answer.

329
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:20,867
[JUSTIN] You know,
you said it yourself.

330
00:20:21,633 --> 00:20:24,000
We both have to protect
our family.

331
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:26,900
But you're not keeping
your word.

332
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:32,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

333
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:34,533
What did Sandro's son say?

334
00:20:35,333 --> 00:20:36,700
Someone had him abducted.

335
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:41,533
He heard them call
their boss "Sir Andy".

336
00:20:41,933 --> 00:20:44,367
And he thought
it was Andy Arellano?

337
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:47,433
Her father had previously
mentioned Uncle Andy.

338
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:50,733
They tortured him to find out
where the treasure was buried.

339
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:51,933
Treasure?

340
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,800
[SCOFFS] What treasure?

341
00:20:53,800 --> 00:21:00,367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

342
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:02,367
There's treasure
here in Hotel 88.

343
00:21:02,767 --> 00:21:03,867
[MARTIN] Treasure?

344
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,567
[HENRI]
Is this Juan's statement?

345
00:21:23,567 --> 00:21:30,400
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:36,800
"I believe the person who
abducted me was Leon Almazan"?

347
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:44,600
What are you doing here?

348
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:46,600
- What else did you hear?
- Justin...

349
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:50,567
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

350
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:52,833
Leon...

351
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:55,867
Does he know, too?

352
00:21:58,933 --> 00:22:00,667
Don't tell me
he knows more than I do.

353
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,033
Justin. Can you stop
being so angry?

354
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:05,833
That thing you're talking about,

355
00:22:05,967 --> 00:22:08,967
it's not just about you,
it's our family's concern, too!

356
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:12,367
So, what about this treasure?

357
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,700
Martin, don't listen to Justin.

358
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:16,667
That treasure isn't real.

359
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:18,600
Then, why is there a map?

360
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:20,833
A map?

361
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:23,667
A map of Hotel 88
left in Sandro's house.

362
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:27,167
Why did he have it
if he wasn't interested in it?

363
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:29,800
Having a map doesn't mean
there's a treasure.

364
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:31,700
Leon...

365
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:35,167
Do you remember that video
that Papa left behind?

366
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:38,933
He said
not to sell the hotel off

367
00:22:39,067 --> 00:22:41,000
because there's
something important in here.

368
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,700
I... I don't know.

369
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:44,567
I don't know
what to think anymore.

370
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:48,333
What if that's the reason
for our fathers' huge fight?

371
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,800
That makes sense.

372
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:56,400
Juan told me
that it's an open secret.

373
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,867
What if Dad knew it, too?

374
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:02,267
Did Juan say
what kind of treasure it is?

375
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:04,167
Is he that sure?

376
00:23:06,467 --> 00:23:07,400
No.

377
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:09,400
See?

378
00:23:11,533 --> 00:23:12,933
But it could be anything!

379
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:15,167
A bag of diamonds?

380
00:23:15,767 --> 00:23:17,567
There's a gold mine here.

381
00:23:17,967 --> 00:23:20,733
What if there's gold
in the hotel?

382
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:23,400
Regardless
of what the treasure is,

383
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:27,900
it may be the reason why Andy
wants to get the hotel so bad.

384
00:23:28,267 --> 00:23:31,167
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

385
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,733
We need to find out what it is.

386
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,533
Or if it's even true or not.

387
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:39,167
This could be one way
of protecting our families

388
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:40,900
against Uncle Andy.

389
00:23:47,367 --> 00:23:48,867
<i> Is this a cabinet, too?</i>

390
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:52,533
<i>Sandro isn't the only one
searching for the treasure.</i>

391
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:54,267
<i> Do we know his accomplice?</i>

392
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:58,600
<i> Why do you want to help us?</i>

393
00:23:58,733 --> 00:24:00,000
<i> Why Hotel 88?</i>

394
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:01,800
Because it has something I want.

395
00:24:01,933 --> 00:24:03,867
<i>- What are you doing here?
- Oh my god, Leon!</i>

396
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,600
<i> Just tell us the truth!</i>

397
00:24:05,733 --> 00:24:07,933
<i> You want the truth? Alright!</i>

398
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:09,000
<i> Hey!</i>

399
00:24:09,133 --> 00:24:10,500
<i>They've been looking for you
for a long time.</i>

400
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:12,800
<i>We're no longer safe
from Uncle Andy.</i>

401
00:24:13,467 --> 00:24:15,467
<i> Syvera, check the back.</i>
